      "note": "To selfish men, the good may make an appeal, and say: \"Look Allah has given you wealth, or influence, or knowledge, or talent. Why not spend some of it in charity, i.e., for the good of your fellow-creatures?\" But the selfish only think of themselves and laugh such teaching to scorn."
