  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "26",
      "note": "In Qur'anic usage, the verb anfaqa (lit., \"he spent\") invariably signifies one's spending on others, or for the good of others, whatever the motive. The ethical importance of this \"spending on others\" is frequently stressed in the Qur'an, and is embodied in the concept of zakah, which denotes \"purifying dues\" or, in its broader sense, \"charity\" (see note 34 on 2:43)."
    }
